    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": "How is that for \u201calter egos\u201d and \u201csplit personalities.\u201d The life of the Christian (as described above) works out like this: the flesh that is \u201ccrucified with Christ\u201d is the physical body that suffers a slow, lingering death. As far as its power over you, it is buried. God doesn\u2019t recognize the flesh; He doesn\u2019t pay any attention to it. So any time you spend serving the flesh is wasted time. It is time serving a corpse. It is lost time, resulting in lost rewards at the Judgment Seat of Christ. In the meantime, there lives in you a new nature. That new nature is given life by the Holy Spirit, who is the Spirit of Christ (Rom. 8:9\u201310); \u201cChrist in you, the hope of glory.\u201d That is why Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]` said in Galatians 2:20, \u201cI am crucified with Christ: nevertheless I live; yet not I, but Christ liveth in me.\u201d When it comes to living the Christian life successfully and having victory over sin, the most important thing you can know is that Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ dwells in your body in the person of the Holy Spirit. That is what gives you the power to overcome temptation. The Corinthians didn\u2019t know that, and as a result, they had the most carnal church in the New Testament (1 Cor. 6:19\u201320). The Satanic counterfeit for that doctrine is \u201clet Christ come into your life .\u201d That phrase has no meaning at all. Every time a lost person comes across a gospel tract or witness and every time the Holy Spirit convicts a sinner of his sin, Christ is involving Himself in that life. I\u2019ll guarantee you that the Lord is so involved in the Devil\u2019s life that Satan doesn\u2019t care for it a bit. If Christ is only \u201cin your life ,\u201d then you are lost; He is in your body, if you are saved. It is not the same thing. Salvation is letting Christ come into your body and making you a new creature in Him. Discipleship is letting Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ take control of the way you live. Unlike the Gospels, in this age (the Church Age), those two don\u2019t necessarily begin at the same time. If you try to be a disciple of Christ without being saved, then you are back in Matthew 7:21\u2013\n22. How is that for \u201calter egos\u201d and \u201csplit personalities.\u201d The life of the Christian (as described above) works out like this: the flesh that is \u201ccrucified with Christ\u201d is the physical body that suffers a slow, lingering death. As far as its power over you, it is buried. God doesn\u2019t recognize the flesh; He doesn\u2019t pay any attention to it. So any time you spend serving the flesh is wasted time. It is time serving a corpse. It is lost time, resulting in lost rewards at the Judgment Seat of Christ. In the meantime, there lives in you a new nature. That new nature is given life by the Holy Spirit, who is the Spirit of Christ [v_Rom_8_9] (Rom. 8:9\u201310); \u201cChrist in you, the hope of glory.\u201d That is why [v_Gal_2_20] Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]` said in Galatians 2:20, \u201cI am crucified with Christ: nevertheless I live; yet not I, but Christ liveth in me.\u201d When it comes to living the Christian life successfully and having victory over sin, the most important thing you can know is that Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ dwells in your body in the person of the Holy Spirit. That is what gives you the power to overcome temptation. The Corinthians didn\u2019t know that, and as a result, they had the most [v_1Co_6_19] carnal church in the New Testament (1 Cor. 6:19\u201320). The Satanic counterfeit for that doctrine is \u201clet Christ come into your life.\u201d That phrase has no meaning at all. Every time a lost person comes across a gospel tract or witness and every time the Holy Spirit convicts a sinner of his sin, Christ is involving Himself in that life. I\u2019ll guarantee you that the Lord is so involved in the Devil\u2019s life that Satan doesn\u2019t care for it a bit. If Christ is only \u201cin your life,\u201d then you are lost; He is in your body, if you are saved. It is not the same thing. Salvation is letting Christ come into your body and making you a new creature in Him. Discipleship is letting Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ take control of the way you live. Unlike the Gospels, in this age (the Church Age), those two don\u2019t necessarily begin at the same time. If you try to be a disciple of Christ without being saved, then you are [v_Mat_7_21] back in Matthew 7:21\u2013",
